      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's more than just \"symbolism\" tho. when u see how the lines converge on the obelisk, it feels like it's meant to funnel something. like a focal point for energy or something. if u look at the angles, they don't just represent ideals, they look like they're actually shaped to pull attention—or something else—down into the center of the city. do u see how the geometry actually functions as a sort of conduit?",
